F Immune System Recognition Last updated Save as PDF Page ID Contributed by Henry JakubowskiProfessor Chemistry at College of St BenedictSt Johns University Contributors and Attributions In this last chapter on binding we will consider the daunting task faced by the immune system to recognize all possible foreign molecules and react to them either by targeting them for elimination or paradoxically to recognize them but not react to them a process called tolerance The same can be said of selfmolecules The immune system must recognize them but not respond to them otherwise autoimmune disease might arise in which the bodys powerful immune system targets self Topic hierarchy Contributors and Attributions Prof Henry Jakubowski College of St BenedictSt Johns University